# Session Awareness

> **Cursor note:** `/onboard` and `/closeout` are available as Cursor skills (imported from `.claude/commands/`). Invoke them the same way you would in Claude Code.

## Before Starting Work

The full onboarding procedure is defined in `~/.claude/commands/onboard.md` and invoked via `/onboard`.

It covers:
1. Update date awareness in Memory MCP
2. Query Memory MCP for project context and preferences
3. Check git status (branch, uncommitted changes, remote branches)
4. Read SESSION_LOG.md (last session, next steps, known issues)
5. Read CHANGELOG.md (unreleased work)
6. Sync external TODO (import pending tasks, detect user additions)
7. Check for pending agent work (unmerged Warp/other agent branches)
8. Present summary and ask for direction

---

## When to Update SESSION_LOG

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| **Major task completion** | Add checkpoint entry after finishing a feature or significant task |
| **24-hour resume** | If resuming after 24+ hours, log what was done before continuing |
| **Explicit request** | User requests a checkpoint or session log update |
| **Session end** | User invokes `/closeout` or requests handoff preparation |

> **Checkpoint vs Full Closeout:** For mid-session milestones, a quick SESSION_LOG entry is sufficient. Full closeout includes git verification, CHANGELOG, external TODO sync, Memory MCP updates, and handoff confirmation.

---

## Session Closeout

The full closeout procedure is defined in `~/.claude/commands/closeout.md` and invoked via `/closeout`.

It covers:
1. Identify accomplishments
2. Check git status (ensure committed and pushed)
3. Update SESSION_LOG.md
4. Update CHANGELOG.md (if project has one)
5. Sync external TODO (e.g., Obsidian task list)
6. Update auto memory (`MEMORY.md`)
7. Update Memory MCP
8. Commit and push documentation updates
9. Confirm with user

---

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Session log read before starting work
- [ ] Accomplishments identified
- [ ] Git status verified (committed and pushed)
- [ ] SESSION_LOG.md updated
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated (if applicable)
- [ ] External TODO synced (if applicable)
- [ ] Auto memory updated (if applicable)
- [ ] Memory MCP updated with stable facts
- [ ] Documentation changes committed and pushed
- [ ] User notified and confirmed
